INSERT INTO `node_revisions` VALUES (87,87,1,'The Queen\'s Birthday Ball','<p>Every year, the Queen\'s Birthday Ball is the most glamorous night-out in the British Association\'s calendar. It is also our major fund-raiser. We are proud to have the generous support of many sponsors from the Seoul business community. Some sponsors provide the goods and services we need to run this fantastic event. Others support our nominated charities directly by donating of cash.<br><br>Every year the theme of the Ball is kept a secret, until the doors are opened to admit the 500 guests to the amazing ballroom. The theme is always connected with our British heritage and on 30 May 2009, the Grand Ballroom of The Grand Hyatt Hotel was transformed into The Great British Seaside. The Ballroom was decorated with colourful beach huts, Union Jack bunting and giant ice-cream cones and guests were entertained with barbershop singing by the The Lightyears.<br><br>The roast beef dinner was followed by a live auction of Manchester United items, Korean art and a signed golf jacket. Big prizes in The Grand Raffle were drawn and then guests poured onto the dance-floor for two storming sets from The Lightyears, who performed on a mock-up of the entrance to Brighton Pier.<br><br>There are some great photos of the evening on this website.<br><br>If you would like to sponsor this event in 2010, please contact us. There are many ways we can work together to give much-needed assistance to the under-privileged whilst also providing the international community with one of its best nights out.</p>','<p>Every year, the Queen\'s Birthday Ball is the most glamorous night-out in the British Association\'s calendar. It is also our major fund-raiser. We are proud to have the generous support of many sponsors from the Seoul business community. Some sponsors provide the goods and services we need to run this fantastic event. Others support our nominated charities directly by donating of cash.<br>','',1267163946,5)